\begin_layout Subsubsection
Objects
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The elements of a simulation (objects) which can be added to the flowsheet
 are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Material Stream
\series default
\emph default
: used to represent matter which enters and leaves the limits of the simulation
 and passes through the unit operations.
 The user should define their conditions and composition in order for DWSIM
 to calculate their properties accordingly;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Energy Stream
\series default
\emph default
: used to represent energy which enters and leaves the limits of the simulation
 and passes through the unit operations;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Mixer
\series default
\emph default
: used to mix up to three material streams into one, while executing all
 the mass and energy balances;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Splitter
\series default
\emph default
: mass balance unit operation - divides a material stream into two or three
 other streams; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Valve
\series default
\emph default
: works like a fixed pressure drop for the process, where the outlet material
 stream properties are calculated beginning from the principle that the
 expansion is an isenthalpic process; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Pipe
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a fluid flow process (mono or two-phase).
 The pipe implementation in DWSIM provides the user with various configuration
 options, including heat transfer to environment or even to the soil in
 buried pipes.
 Two correlations for pressure drop calculations are available: Beggs &
 Brill and Lockhart & martinelli.
 Both reduces to Darcy equation in the case of single-phase flow;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Pump
\series default
\emph default
: used to provide energy to a liquid stream in the form of pressure.
 The process is isenthalpic, and the non-idealities are considered according
 to the pump efficiency, which is defined by the user; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Tank
\series default
\emph default
: in the current version of DWSIM, the tank works like a fixed pressure
 drop for the process;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Separator Vessel
\series default
\emph default
: used to separate the vapor and liquid phases of a stream into two other
 distinct streams;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Compressor
\series default
\emph default
: used to provide energy to a vapor stream in the form of pressure.
 The ideal process is isentropic (constant entropy) and the non-idealities
 are considered according to the compressor efficiency, which is defined
 by the user; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Expander
\series default
\emph default
: the expander is used to extract energy from a high-pressure vapor stream.
 The ideal process is isentropic (constant entropy) and the non-idealities
 are considered according to the expander efficiency, which is defined by
 the user; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Heater
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a stream heating process;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Cooler
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a stream cooling process;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Conversion Reactor
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a reactor where conversion reactions occur;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Equilibrium Reactor
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a reactor where equilibrium reactions occur;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
PFR
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a Plug Flow Reactor (PFR);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
CSTR
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a Continuous-Stirred Tank Reactor (CSTR);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Shortcut Column
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a simple distillation column with approximate results using
 shorcut calculations;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Distillation Column
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a distillation column using rigorous thermodynamic models;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Absorption Column
\series default
\emph default
: simulates an absorption column using rigorous thermodynamic models;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Refluxed Absorber
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a refluxed absorber column using rigorous thermodynamic models;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Reboiled Absorber
\series default
\emph default
: simulates a reboiled absorber column using rigorous thermodynamic models.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\emph on
Heat Exchanger:
\series default
\emph default
 simulates a countercurrent heat exchanger using rigorous thermodynamic
