\begin_layout Subsubsection
Simulation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
DWSIM is a sequential modular process simulator, that is, all calculations
 are made in a per-module basis, according to the connections between the
 objects.
 The calculator checks if an object has all of its properties defined and,
 if yes, passes the data for the downstream object and calculates it, repeating
 the process in a loop until it reaches an object that doesn't have any
 of its dowstream connections attached to any object.
 This way, the entire flowsheet can be calculated as many times as necessary
 without having to "tell" DWSIM which object must be calculated.
 In fact, this is done indirectly if the user define all the properties
 and make all connections between objects correctly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
DWSIM's calculation starts when the user edits a property which defines
